sec.p:
Historically, HER is the most studied, particularly in acidic solutions. By contrast, limited research has been conducted on HER in alkaline solutions, that is, the operation condition of chlor-alkali electrolyzers, mainly due to the complicated reaction mechanism. The possible pathway of HER in highly alkaline media includes the following steps: electro-reduction of water molecules and hydrogen adsorption (Volmer reaction, Step 1); electrochemical desorption of hydrogen (Heyrovsky reaction, Step 2); chemical desorption (Tafel reaction, Step 3).
